commit_message:
Support for setting boot mode in pxe_ilo driver

This commit adds support for setting boot mode in pxe_ilo
driver with the help of iloclient.
It modifies the PXEAndIloDriver so that it uses
IloPower for power management,
IloPXEDeploy for image deployment,
IloPXEVendorPassthru for vendorpassthru,
IPMITool console and management interfaces.

Change-Id: Ifb29c6b4c60ce17a7e5c15af7fb62e1c1e1c9ad7
Implements: blueprint uefi-boot-for-ironic

re-approving, failed to merge because of a jgit bug aparently (see the convo snipet from #openstack-infra):

<ndipanov> fungi, that really sucks then because it colided with something on it's own branch... tht's a serious bug imho
<fungi> ndipanov: cgit and jgit aren't identical in their merge calculation algorithms and occasionally we'll run across a conflict which zuul thinks is non-encroaching but gerrit then disagrees
<ndipanov> sigh
<fungi> ndipanov: it will need to be rebased before gerrit will allow it to merge
<ndipanov> fungi, so that means back of the (28 hour long) line, right?
<fungi> ndipanov: was it part of a long patch series? we *have* seen what seems to be a bug in jgit where an n-way merge fails opaquely claiming there's a conflict if n>~4
<ndipanov> yes it was
<fungi> ndipanov: yes, it will need to go back through check and gate
<ndipanov> 9 patches
<fungi> ndipanov: avoiding long patch series or spacing out their approvals also helps avoid that bug
<ndipanov> fungi, I see
<ndipanov> IMHO this is a serious bug that basically makes the FFE rush not an option for larger features"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-11 15:27:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 26: Verified+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-18 11:43:48.000000000', 'message': 'Method for getting NUMA usage from an instance

At present, neither ResourceTracker nor HostManager use objects
consistently. Due to that - we need to handle numa_topology being both
a json blob, instance of VirtNUMATopology, or None at different places
in the code. In addition to that - it can either be a field in a dict,
a NovaObject attribute, or even an attribute on an object that does not
support .get() interface.

Poluting the VirtNUMAHostTopology.get_usage_from_instances breaks
separation of concerns, and is just poor design, but we do need to go
through the same logic in several places, so we add a convenience method
that knows how to deal with all the different combinations described
above.

Change-Id: I91c3a77153ef8e5e701d3bc7af37ff0a2943fc0c
Blueprint: virt-driver-numa-placement

commit_message:
Method for getting NUMA usage from an instance

At present, neither ResourceTracker nor HostManager use objects
consistently. Due to that - we need to handle numa_topology being both
a json blob, instance of VirtNUMATopology, or None at different places
in the code. In addition to that - it can either be a field in a dict,
a NovaObject attribute, or even an attribute on an object that does not
support .get() interface.

Polluting the VirtNUMAHostTopology.get_usage_from_instances breaks
separation of concerns, and is just poor design, but we do need to go
through the same logic in several places, so we add a convenience method
that knows how to deal with all the different combinations described
above.

We also add a separated out method for getting the numa_topology out of
all the possible ways we use instance currently, as it will be useful
for filtering to know if the instance actually has a defined
numa_topology.

Change-Id: I91c3a77153ef8e5e701d3bc7af37ff0a2943fc0c
Blueprint: virt-driver-numa-placement

commit_message:
Add oslo.serialization

Add the new Oslo library for managing object serialization. This code is
moving out of the incubator into a library, so projects that wish to
continue using it need the requirement added to the global list first.

NOTE: this is needed for clients installed from master using oslo.serialization.

Conflicts:
	global-requirements.txt

Partial-Bug: #1366748

Change-Id: Iff29ce2e88cddc2332229cfbbc518251dd2c76f3
(cherry picked from commit 2ce3f8259b56410bdd73deca09b7963f4a46e1da)

commit_message:
Remove the objectify decorator

The objectify decorator was used to convert DB objects into RPC objects,
but it's not being used anymore since out objects API already has
correspondent methods to match the dbapi ones.

Also, since dbapi methods didn't get a context the decorator was forming
bad RPC objects without a context stored within it.

Change-Id: I892ab6ee2236af040c7f8effcfdfecb293e13ab6
Partial-Bug: #1314732

commit_message:
Use 'configure' instead of 'enable' when talking about kernel function configuration

Because we enable and disable kernel networking functions we should
use 'configure' instead of 'enable'.

Change-Id: Ia0aa260bfa49c076ab62fd3a161b986140c7912d

commit_message:
Call unbind_snat_servicenode from schedule router

Refactor to move the call to plugin.unbind_snat_servicenode from
schedule_snat_router to _schedule_router.  This is a move to pave the
way for removing hints from schedule router.

Partial-bug: #1353266
Partial-bug: #1356639
Co-Authored-By: Swaminathan Vasudevan <swaminathan.vasudevan@hp.com>

Change-Id: I062d8cc3cb870bbaa033d5b107a7dd868dfafa19

This is breaking for me on tagged interfaces because VLAN=yes is needed for the ifcfg file.'}, {'account_id': 6918, 'date': '2014-07-22 10:39:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

Hi we really appreciate this patch as it is very useful but to confirm what Michael has said, would prefer this patch is not merged as it still needs work.

Currently the patch creates replaces an existing /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-xxxN with a new one that creates the xxxN interface as an OVSPort. 
This is good and seems to work correctly. However it does not preserve all the information in the new ifcfg-xxxN script.

For example,

VLAN=yes and ONPARENT=yes is missing in the new ifcfg-xxxN script, and values like GATEWAY= are not transferred to the new ifcfg-br-ex script.'}, {'account_id': 11166, 'date': '2014-07-23 14:37:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-23 14:37:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Hi guys, the new patch is very good. Thankyou! One small thing I noticed, is that now, the ip address which was previously transferred from the xxxN interface to br-ex is now listed on both interfaces.

e.g. 

If we had an interface eth3 with the ipaddress 192.168.100.100 previously this ip would be transferred to br-ex and no longer appear in the configuration for eth3. Now the ipaddress is configured on both eth3 and br-ex. 

This does not seem to affect functionality, but I thought I would note it as the behaviour has changed from patchset 7. 

Everything else is great.'}, {'account_id': 6994, 'date': '2014-07-24 08:04:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10:

I think there is a problem here with how DHCP interfaces are added to an OVS bridge.  I have now seen two instances where an OVS bridge was configured with OVSBOOTPROTO=dhcp but with no OVSDHCPINTERFACES setting, which means the bridge never comes up.

I am suspicious of the dynamic? function, which is checking the interface itself rather than the interface configuration file.  It seems like dynamic? should be reporting on the status of BOOTPROTO in the existing configuration file, rather than the current state of the interface (which may or may not reflect the intended configuration at the time puppet is running).'}, {'account_id': 6525, 'date': '2014-09-01 03:19:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 19:

Replying previous comment from Lars

Regarding the OVSDHCPINTERFACES issue:
It's working on RHEL7.
But effectively iproute2 is broken on RHEL6: for instance 'ip addr show dynamic' doesn't filter dhcp interfaces.
I'll make a patch for that one. Thanks for the catch!

Regarding the 'dynamic?' method:
There are pros and cons between checking an interface 'running config' vs its 'saved config'.
One should assume a properly configured system to have its running status reflected into its stored configuration.
The bottom line, not matter what approach is taken, the fact there isn't an API way to configure network on Linux.
In the meantime, checking network interface status directly via kernel (/sys/class/net in link? method) or indirectly via 'ip' command is, I think, robust enough as opposed to parse configuration file, but again, this is a choice."}, {'account_id': 6525, 'date': '2014-09-01 04:47:50.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 20.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-09-01 05:18:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 20: Verified+1

commit_message:
Refacfored a more suitable ovs_redhat provider

  - Added a helper class/library to handle ifcfg content

  - Removed keep_ip and sleep parameters, replaced by
    automatic behaviour

  - No need for a redhat vs_bridge provider

  - Only port/bridge associated with a phyical interface get a
    ifcfg file managed

  - Requires Puppet 2.7.8+
    Not using optional_commands anymore

When the bridge is associated with an active physical interface
  - It will be initially populated from the existing interface
    file, inheriting its parameters

Change-Id: I584fb1442de9a760b3a092f96cbfcbcd6776fdba

commit_message:
Catch NotImplementedError on reset_network for xen

This patch adds a @messaging.expected_exceptions(NotImplementedError)
decorator around reset_network as xen raises NotImplementedError here.

Change-Id: Ib1a0cb400ea89f387cd43630d8c647bf5c99f7ab
Closes-bug: #1306404

commit_message:
Replace fakes.FakeClient inheritence with Mock

NovaFakeClient had fakes.FakeClient as a super classes.

This dependency broke the build as the interface was not
well defined

Replace the super classe FakeClient with MagicMock and implement
the local return types as mock object

Closes-bug: 1364515
Change-Id: I746daf38f985eba824a5a0759f450766b08b2dab

commit_message:
Shortened tablenames constants in Neutron driver

Previously, the constants for tablenames in the Neutron
driver were all prefixed with NEUTRON_, e.g.
NEUTRON_PORTS_SECURITY_GROUPS.  This prefix is unnecessary
since it is clear from context.

This change removes the prefix throughout the codebase.

Change-Id: Ib9cea8243886523ad639f7151ac593fc3ad21804

commit_message:
Fixed Neutron translation of external_gateway_info

Previously, the translation of the router's external_gateway_info
basically either returned True or False, indicating whether or
not the external_gateway_info was None or not.

This change properly translates external_gateway_info
into either None or a hash table.  It also adds tests
for router and security_group translations.

Change-Id: Ie482d57d6e644bffc9cf0f57a578f04a6e5fabbe

commit_message:
Added schema interface to datasource drivers

Previously, the Nova and Neutron datasource drivers had
different ways of exporting their schemas.

This change introduces an interface for exposing a schema.
The interface consists of one method, 'get_schema', which
returns a dictionary that maps each tablename to a tuple
of column names.

Change-Id: I21d6f5926560a2e720a4e8240381237bdacdfe70

commit_message:
Cleaned up Neutron and Nova drivers

The old drivers were a bit hard for people to understand.

This change simplifies the drivers a bit and improves things like
variable naming.

Change-Id: Ie3f81b825af144cf4483c5cad82099658fe5dee9

sync_command and async_command in ironic_python_agent/extensions/base.py
are implemented so that they change decorated method signature,
which is really bad practice. Example:

@sync_command
def orig_method(self, **kw):
...

sync_command decorator returns lambda which has one additional
argument 'command_name'

def sync_command(func):
    def decorated(self, command_name, **kw):
         ...
         func(self, **kw)
         ...

both decorators and func.__name__ is used as an argument for
AsyncCommandResult instead. Every call of decorated functions is fixed,
BaseAgentExtension.execute is updated to not send this extra argument.

commit_message:
Enhance decorators in agent and automate creation of command_map

sync_command and async_command in ironic_python_agent/extensions/base.py
are implemented so that they change decorated method signature,
which is really bad practice. Example:

@sync_command
def orig_method(self, **kw):
...

sync_command decorator returns lambda which has one additional
argument 'command_name'

def sync_command(func):
    def decorated(self, command_name, **kw):
         ...
         func(self, **kw)
         ...
    return decorated

Additional parameter 'command_name' is moved from decorated function to
decorator signature in both decorators. Every call of decorated functions
is fixed, BaseAgentExtension.execute is updated to not send this extra
argument. BaseAgentExtension.__init__ automatically generates command_map
from decorated methods.

Change-Id: Iff0f495bc8d9c731892feb0f4759a7f10ee76328
Closes-Bug: 1314148

commit_message:
Configure enabled and disabled extensions in tempest

This patch adds support for configuring the api_extensions
option of the various feature-$service-(enabled|disabled)
sections in tempest's configuration file.

Please note that enabled extensions for the object storage
service are specified in tempest using the discoverable_apis
configuration options.

Partially-implements: Blueprint branchless-tempest-extensions

Change-Id: Ib64c0a474b153f42f3a4a427d86275c85f107997

loose this information when we convert VimFaultException to a specific

Change-Id: I42a50b60fc74383a2c1d9b907125ff17795ce440

commit_message:
Add 'details' property to VMwareDriverException

The details property of the VimFaultException is very important and we
loose this information when we convert VimFaultException to a specific
subclass of VMwareDriverException. This patch fix this by propagating
the details to VMwareDriverException.

Change-Id: I42a50b60fc74383a2c1d9b907125ff17795ce440

commit_message:
Add two new functions to manipulate with lists

Add list.skip(count) and list.take(count) functions to collect only
a part of original list.

Change-Id: Ic730713f0baad64385e37b36e378615482c7a75d
Closes-bug: #1362892

commit_message:
Skipping dashboard test to unblock gate

The error is only seen in the gate when run in parallel, to ease
contention on the gate, temporarily disabling until a proper
solution has been determined.

Related-Bug: #1345955
Change-Id: I3b61895e3f2b0d96488bef56dc0c6105a212d4dc

commit_message:
nova: support setting scheduler_host_manager

Adds support for setting scheduler_host_manager if
it is set via heat metadata. Previously this
value was hard coded based upon the use of
either Ironic or Nova baremetal.

The motivation here is to be able to use the new Ironic driver
location in the Nova tree.

Change-Id: Id4ca7f90cd85129727e65d0d09f274f3a00d4ebe

commit_message:
Use unlogged batches instead of atomic batches

MagnetoDB API doesn't require atomic batches
so we can improve performance by using unlogged batches

Implements: bp improve-batch-write-performance

Change-Id: I139358ad6424095243f36b7f2a619ed0243ecdfe

Add ceilometer volume and glance notifications ostf tests 

Added ceilometer volume measurements: volume, volume.size
Added ceilometer glance measurements: image, image.size, image.update,
image.upload, image.delete

Partially implements: blueprint ceilometer-ostf-notification-tests

Change-Id: Ie9f3a518bc5e24a4289220385a1e6e0ac0a41305

commit_message:
Add uefi boot mode support in IloVirtualMediaIscsiDeploy

The following functionality need to be added in iLO driver:
  - Add set_boot_mode function to iLO driver to switch between
    bios and uefi boot modes.
  - Validate boot_mode for IloVirtualMediaIscsiDeploy driver.

Change-Id: Ic8496a2d97aab6634b573c85d379b446c49e04b9
Implements: blueprint uefi-boot-for-ironic

- gate-oslo.db-tox-sqla_09 http://logs.openstack.org/89/121089/1/check/gate-oslo.db-tox-sqla_09/9540e73 : SUCCESS in 1m 39s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 11816, 'date': '2014-09-12 14:45:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Not creating the .pyc files changes the behavior of the interpreter in subtle ways, such as smoking out code that is implicitly relying upon the ordering of dictionaries, and it also impacts performance.    I'd be very concerned if the practice of never using .pyc files anywhere in any openstack testing becomes commonplace, and we then release our code to the public where it will run in an entirely new context that is never otherwise exercised.


The Python interpreter is very smart about ensuring that .pyc files stay fresh with regards to their corresponding .py file.  The bug report refers to the phenomenon of deleting files and switching branches as the source of the issue, and in my experience, this usually happens when files have been renamed into packages or vice versa.    I would *far* prefer an approach that simply locates all non-paired .pyc files up front and deletes them, leaving the vast majority of the Python interpreter's work unchanged.   This is a simple script to write and we can have it as, for example, an oslo.utils command that just runs up front from a tox.ini.

The issue of libraries installed in the .tox directories is a non-issue; we don't check out code into those directories, we only install packages, so there are no stale .pyc files due to switching branches or deleting files since this does not occur within .tox."}, {'account_id': 5638, 'date': '2014-09-12 16:03:11.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Do not allow to create 5.0-based environments

5.0 releases don't have version suffix, so filter them out by
comparing release version to '2014.1'

Change-Id: I7a1c1e6148e145ba6e89e8d451e21b5de67a4662
Closes-bug: 1368100

commit_message:
Fixed regression in file writing

Flags got moved from a to a+ but it's unsupported by ZipFile.
Changed the name of the write_backend variable but forgot to change it
in the OSRF writer.

Change-Id: I6ddf14c07e84af0a5e5b0994d72a8bfc506adce0

commit_message:
Debug semaphore creation

Just adds some debugging around when semaphores are created so we
can tell if they're being double-locked or just destroyed and
recreated.

Change-Id: Ia266fbdc87fcacdbc3eddcab83a3a39caff6c19c

But keystone depends on keystoneclient itself, right? So pip should handle it when fetching dependencies for keystone.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-18 14:51:29.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Ihar - when a version of keystoneclient is released that has the oslo.utils dependency then pip will handle it, but there will be a time where the change is in keystoneclient master but isn't released. So we could require a new keystoneclient release as soon as the requirement change is merged -- then we wouldn't have to do this."}, {'account_id': 4, 'date': '2014-08-18 14:55:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-18 14:59:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Brant, ok, I get the scenario of failure now. So why not installing oslo.utils from master the same way we do for other oslo libraries, like oslo.rootwrap or oslo.messaging?'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-18 15:12:11.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Ihar - I don't know how we would install oslo.utils from master like olso.messaging... do you have some example code you could point at?

Also, I didn't expect this to pass jenkins until https://review.openstack.org/#/c/114844/ was merged... wonder why it didn't fail?"}, {'account_id': 9098, 'date': '2014-08-18 15:16:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 9098, 'date': '2014-08-18 15:21:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@Brant

I think this passed Jenkins since the requirement for oslo.utils was reverted in python-keystoneclient:

  https://review.openstack.org/#/c/114825

Without the merge of the global-requirements.txt change, I believe that the oslo.utils requirement here in keystone's requirements.txt is simply ignored.  The logs from the Jenkins job doesn't show oslo.utils being installed."}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-18 16:48:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Brant, https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/lib/oslo#L41'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-18 17:29:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Ihar - Keystone does the same thing -- https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/blob/master/lib/keystone#L424 -- except it does setup_develop instead of setup_install.'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-18 17:50:07.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Brant, the point is that if devstack will install oslo.utils from master to /opt/stack/ for you, it will be available without explicit dependency you define here.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-18 18:03:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Ihar - Are you saying that you'd prefer that devstack in stable/havana is changed to install oslo.utils rather than this change?"}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-08-19 08:39:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Yes. I would prefer that it does it for all branches (master, icehouse, havana), now that we rely on it. Without having oslo.utils tested in gate with devstack, we potentially loose regressions that could be caught in gate.'}, {'account_id': 8978, 'date': '2014-09-12 10:43:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 9656, 'date': '2014-09-12 14:15:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

For Icehouse, I've cherry-picked the appropriate devstack change: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/121128/ As for Havana, it will be closed after the last release the next week, so I don't think we need to spend any time to solve the issue for the branch."}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-09-12 15:03:47.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Not doing this for havana since it will be out of service long before the keystoneclient change is merged.'}]

commit_message:
add oslo.utils for testing with Keystoneclient master

stable/* tests run with keystoneclient master and
master keystoneclient will be changing to require
oslo.utils.

Conflicts:

	test-requirements.txt

Change-Id: Ia29f69731d4dc79e8fc5d14afa932558de387799
Closes-Bug: #1357652
(cherry picked from commit 087550b02b63fdd6ffd5114829591f9b859853ac)

commit_message:
Add code/api documentation

Once we use the pbr based build to generate files, we prune
the indexes to remove references to code we would like to
hide like the common modules and private modules in conf.py.
We reuse the same excluded_patterns variable that is already
used in Sphinx and filter these modules from autoindex.rst

Change-Id: I4baea1efa227ef14bc6706d59ff3dcad93c2eacc
Closes-Bug: #1364140

commit_message:
Add API to enable calling module to register an exception

In certain cases the application, for example Nova, may need to treat
a VC exception that is currently not supported by oslo.vmware.

This will enable the application to dynamically add exceptions and then
remove them when oslo.vmware is updated to support the new exception.

The patch also fixes a typo with the exception fault handling.

Change-Id: I332a4ff2ac2c6d4e6ac88bbd067ef0d4e659ffa3

commit_message:
Add mechanism for generation action parameters

 * Add getting human-readable params for adding
   to action
 * Add getting description for action
 * Parameters and description is already generated
   for std_actions
 * Unit tests

TODO:
  * Add the same for OpenStack Actions

Change-Id: I2f2a8ebe3bc3e75ab53f985adcecb59c0f1d7d8b

Add oslo.utils and oslo.serialization

Install the oslo.utils and oslo.serialization libraries from source so
the gate tests run against master.

commit_message:
Revert "Pull in patched eventlet to fix Second Simultaneous errors"

This reverts commit 0011e19c15cee09c21a1ec5f772a480a677201b9.

Eventlet version 0.15.1 has been released with the fix to the
